02/12/2004
ROME, Italy -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy said Wednesday (1 December) that the accession of Southeast European countries to NATO structures would guarantee lasting peace and stability in the region. In his address to the 50th General Assembly of the Atlantic Treaty Association (ATA), Passy said he hoped Albania, Croatia and Macedonia would join NATO soon. He praised ATA's role in developing democracy in the region in the years since the fall of the Iron Curtain. (BTA, BNT - 01/12/04)
